<section class="tradeoffs-block">
  <p class="eyebrow">Design tradeoffs</p>
  <h2 class="section-title">What this design chooses on purpose</h2>

  <div class="trade-grid">
    <article class="trade-card">
      <h3>Segmentation over convenience</h3>
      <p>More firewall work and more planning, but clearer trust boundaries and safer testing paths.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="trade-card">
      <h3>VPN-first admin access</h3>
      <p>Less convenience than public management exposure, but dramatically better control of the management plane.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="trade-card">
      <h3>Contained aquarium zone</h3>
      <p>More operational overhead, but much better safety for malware detonation, capture, and rollback-based analysis.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="trade-card">
      <h3>Clustered, not magically HA</h3>
      <p>Cluster membership gives coordination, not automatic resilience. HA still requires deliberate storage and failover design.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

